title: Alaska tribal members get back totem pole taken by actor
text: > Top News Alaska tribal members get back totem pole taken by actor Tlingit Tribe members from Klawock, Alaska Jonathan Rowan, left, and Eva Rowan perform a dance at the Honolulu Museum of Arts, Thursday, Oct. 22, 2015, in Honolulu. A totem pole, stolen by actor John Barrymore during a sailing trip to Alaska in 1931, was returned to the Tribe today by the Honolulu Museum of Arts today, where it was on display since the early 1980s. The totem pole was carved by the ancestors of the Tlingit Tribe. (AP Photo/Marco Garcia)
